The article discusses the Build America Investment Initiative, a government-wide initiative launched by the Obama administration to increase infrastructure investment and economic growth. The initiative includes the creation of the Build America Transportation Investment Center, which serves as a one-stop shop for cities and states looking to use innovative financing and partnerships with the private sector to support transportation infrastructure. The article also highlights the importance of investing in infrastructure to create jobs, provide certainty to states and communities, help American businesses, and grow the economy. The initiative aims to tap into private capital to revitalize US infrastructure and increase the pipeline of public-private partnerships. The article provides case studies of successful PPPs in Colorado and Florida and mentions the GROW AMERICA Act, a proposed transportation reauthorization plan to provide stable funding for highways, bridges, transit, and rail systems.